    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Shopping List — Home Assistant → Mealie\n\nListens for HA shopping list events (via HA automation + REST command)\nand pushes changes to Mealie's shopping list.\n\n**Webhook:** POST /webhook/ha-shopping-sync\n\n**HA setup required:**\n1. Add `rest_command` to `configuration.yaml`\n2. Add automation triggered by `shopping_list_updated` event\n   (see plan doc for YAML examples)\n\n**Expected payload:**\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"add|update|remove\",\n  \"item_name\": \"Milk\",\n  \"item_complete\": false,\n  \"source\": \"homeassistant\"\n}\n```\n\n**Environment variables used:**\n- `MEALIE_URL` — Mealie base URL\n- `MEALIE_API_TOKEN` — Mealie Long-Lived API Token\n\n**Loop prevention:**\n- Payloads with `source: \"n8n\"` are skipped\n- Created items get `extras.synced_from = \"homeassistant\"`",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 520
      },
